.TH "WEAKMAP.SET" "3JS" "September 22, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WeakMap.set \- WeakMap.prototype.set()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]set()\f[B]\f[R] method of \f[CR]WeakMap\f[R] instances
adds a new entry with a specified key and value to this
\f[CR]WeakMap\f[R], or updates an existing entry if the key already
exists.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] weakmap = \f[B]new\f[R] WeakMap();
\f[B]const\f[R] object1 = {};
\f[B]const\f[R] object2 = {};

weakmap.set(object1, \(dqfoo\(dq);
weakmap.set(object2, \(dqbar\(dq);

console.log(weakmap.get(object1));
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dqfoo\(dq\f[R]

console.log(weakmap.get(object2));
\f[I]// Expected output: \(dqbar\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
set(key, value)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]key\f[R]
The key of the entry to add to or modify within the \f[CR]WeakMap\f[R]
object.
Must be either an object or a non\-registered symbol.
Object keys are compared by reference, not by value.
.TP
\f[B]value\f[R]
The value of the entry to add to or modify within the \f[CR]WeakMap\f[R]
object.
Can be any value.
.SS Return value
The \f[CR]WeakMap\f[R] object.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]TypeError\f[R]
Thrown if \f[CR]key\f[R] is not an object or a non\-registered symbol.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using set()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] wm = \f[B]new\f[R] WeakMap();
\f[B]const\f[R] obj = {};

\f[I]// Add new elements to the WeakMap\f[R]
wm.set(obj, \(dqfoo\(dq).set(window, \(dqbar\(dq); \f[I]// chainable\f[R]

\f[I]// Update an element in the WeakMap\f[R]
wm.set(obj, \(dqbaz\(dq);

\f[I]// Using a non\-registered symbol as key\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] sym = Symbol(\(dqfoo\(dq);
wm.set(sym, \(dqbaz\(dq);
wm.set(Symbol.iterator, \(dqqux\(dq);
.EE
